FBIS4-35578 "drnes106_l_94018" FBIS-NES-94-106 Daily Report 31 May 1994 ISRAEL Tourism Minister Leaves for Japan, S. Korea, China Tourism Minister Leaves for Japan, S. Korea, China TA3105114494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 31 May 94 TA3105114494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el English BFN [Text] Tourism Minister 'Uzi Bar'am leaves today for Japan, South Korea, and China. Bar'am will meet with his counterparts in these countries to promote tourism with Israel. The Tourism Ministry says in China he is due to sign a cooperation agreement, and in Seoul he'll meet with a group of businessmen interested in investing in tourism in Israel.
